theorem Topology.union_interiors_union_frontier_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (Aᶜ) ∪ frontier A =
      (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- Rewrite the union of the two interiors using the existing lemma.
  have h₁ :
      interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (Aᶜ) =
        (closure (A : Set X) \ interior A)ᶜ :=
    Topology.union_interiors_eq_compl_boundary (A := A)
  -- Rewrite the frontier of `A`.
  have h₂ :
      frontier (A : Set X) =
        closure (A : Set X) \ interior A :=
    Topology.frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (A := A)
  -- Assemble the pieces and use the complement–self union law.
  calc
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (Aᶜ) ∪ frontier A
        = (closure (A : Set X) \ interior A)ᶜ ∪
          (closure (A : Set X) \ interior A) := by
          simpa [h₁, h₂, Set.union_left_comm, Set.union_comm, Set.union_assoc]
    _ = (Set.univ : Set X) := Set.compl_union_self _

theorem Topology.closure_frontier_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (frontier (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- The frontier of `A` is contained in `closure A`; taking closures
  -- preserves this inclusion.
  exact closure_mono (Topology.frontier_subset_closure (A := A))

theorem Topology.closure_frontier_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (frontier (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- `frontier A` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h : frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h' : closure (frontier (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (closure A) := closure_mono h
  simpa [closure_closure] using h'
